<TITLE> BSF kill Bangladeshi at Panchagarh border </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Panchagarh, Feb 06 (bdnews24.com)  India's Border Security Force reportedly killed a Bangladeshi near the Tetulia border in Panchagarh district on Saturday. The dead man was identified by locals as Farid, 28, son of Dabir Uddin of Sharialjot village in Tetulia Upazila. Farid and other villagers were working in a field near Border Pillar No 442 when BSF 103rd Battalion, based at Haftiganj Border Out Post, fired about twelve rounds of gunfire, the villagers said. Family members said Farid died in the spot, while others escaped. BSF took the dead body into Indian territory, where it was being held at the Haftiganj camp, the family said. Farid's father Dabir Uddin told bdnews24.com he had sent a written statement to BDR to get back his son's dead body. Nipen Chandra Das, company commander of Tetulia BDR Camp, told bdnews24.com that Dabir Uddin had written a letter to us abuts missing his son. "We have also tried to communicate with BSF by letter on this matter." Local union parishad chairman Jahangir Alam said: "Farid's father informed me about his missing son. I cannot say anything before the dead body is produced and identified." Earlier in the week, BSF reportedly traded fire with BDR and abducted a Bangladeshi border from Jaintapur in Sylhet district on Thursday. The Indian border force handed back the BDR man following a flag meeting. bdn
